## Style Improvements

### Current Color Scheme

```css
/* Light Theme */
--bg-primary: #f4f5f7;      /* Main background */
--text-title: #f29f67;      /* Title text (orange) */
--text-body: #1e1e2c;       /* Body text */
--container-bg: #ffffff;    /* Container background */
--icon-color: #4d4d4d;      /* Icon color */
--hover-bg: #faeedb;        /* Button hover background */
```

### Potential Color Palettes

#### Vibrant Orange-Purple Theme

```css
--primary: #ff6348;         /* Vibrant orange */
--secondary: #430f44;       /* Deep purple */
--bg-light: #f7f5f4;        /* Light background */
--accent-light: #vffdad2;   /* Light orange accent */
```

#### Modern Teal Theme

```css
--primary: #6dcbc3;         /* Teal */
--bg-dark: #07111f;         /* Dark background */
--hover-dark: #0a242e;      /* Hover state dark */
```

#### Professional Light Theme

```css
--bg-primary: #f4f5f7;      /* Light gray background */
--text-primary: #1e1e2c;    /* Dark text */
--accent: #f29f67;          /* Orange accent */
--container: #ffffff;       /* White containers */
```

## Future Enhancements

- [ ] Implement theme switcher with multiple color schemes
- [ ] Add smooth transitions between color themes
- [ ] Create consistent hover effects across components
- [ ] Implement responsive typography system
- [ ] Add animation to color transitions

## Design Guidelines

1. Maintain consistent spacing and padding
2. Ensure sufficient color contrast for accessibility
3. Use color schemes to create visual hierarchy
4. Implement responsive design breakpoints
5. Add subtle animations for interactions

## Notes

- Test all color combinations for accessibility (WCAG 2.1)
- Consider dark mode variations for each color palette
- Document final color scheme decisions
- Create a style guide for consistent implementation
